Meridian Diagnostics Inc said itfinalized a licensing agreement with the University of Arizonafor the production of a test kit that detects Giardia lamblia,a major cause of traveler's diarrhea.    Giardia is a common parasite found in water and Meridiansaid it is the most common parasite in the U.S. It said itexpects to release the product to the hospital market in late1987.    It also said new government regulations indicate asignificant need for a product to screen public water surpliesfor this parasite. Reuter&#3;